<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF2FFECE2B10345FCE1FC66" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF2FFECE2B10345FCE1FC66" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF2FFECE2F00345FB0AFCFA" box="[970,1193,799,825]" name="Russia" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="9106F844FFF2FFECE5830345FA3EFCFA" box="[1209,1437,799,825]" country="Russia" name="Volgograd" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Volgograd Province</collectingRegion>
Olkhovsky district, Kamenny Brod] is figured by the authorities both upper and underside (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE5A60319FAF8FC9E" author="Korb, S. K. &amp; Stradomsky, B. V. &amp; Kuznetsov, G." box="[1180,1371,834,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" pagination="140 - 145" refId="ref9752" refString="Korb, S. K., Stradomsky, B. V. &amp; Kuznetsov, G. (2015) Two new subspecies of Melitaea ornata Christoph, 1893 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae) from Europe and Middle Asia. Amurian zoological journal, VII (2), 140 - 145." type="journal article" year="2015">
Korb 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE5E50319FAB3FC9E" box="[1247,1296,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
: plate 1: figs 5 &amp; 6). The specimens photographed (
<figureCitation id="CBF92A23FFF2FFECE39E033DFCFDFC42" box="[676,862,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1710,1734]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-121@9.[151,1436,381,1687]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. 17, Holotype of Melitaea phoebe abbas, Gross &amp; Ebert, 1975. © R. Trusch. 18, Allotype of Melitaea phoebe abbas, Gross &amp; Ebert, 1975. © Alipanah. 19, Holotype of Melitaea ornata adversaria Korb, Stradomsky &amp; Kuznetsov, 2015. 20, Paratype of Melitaea ornata reliquiae Korb, Stradomsky &amp; Kuznetsov, 2015. Figs 19, 20 © S.K. Korb, B.V. Stradomsky &amp; G.V. Kuznetsov.A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577646/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Figs 20 A, B, C</figureCitation>
) clearly show the wing morphology and spatulate antennae, characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE0F403D1FD9DFC67" authorityName=", Russell &amp; Tennent" authorityYear="2016" box="[462,574,907,932]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE0F403D1FD9DFC67" box="[462,574,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE3FF03D1FC98FC66" box="[709,827,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE3FF03D1FC98FC66" box="[709,827,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
